Small landmasses meander through the still and lightless swamp. Towering black cypress trees loom over the bayou, with thick curtains of moss streaming from their branches. The only sound to be heard is the occasional soft, lapping of water. From time to time quick, black shadows flit overhead or dart suddenly out of sight at the edge of vision - but you never seem to get a good look at them.
The water of the Plane of Shadow is so cold you wonder how it isn't frozen. It invokes a burning sensation that in mere seconds threatens to make you numb.

You meditate on this little island for a while, letting the mire's energies flow over you, For a moment you covered in shadows. This exhilarating feeling makes you wonder if you can regain it in the prime by drawing the surrounding shadows to flow over you like this. Perhaps its time to return to your instructor.
